Many applications require a very precise time measurement.

currentTimeMillis() returns current time in milliseconds since Epoch Time, in Long form.

long startTime = System.currentTimeMillis();
long estimatedTime 
  = System.currentTimeMillis() - startTime;

nanoTime() returns the current value of the most precise available system timer, in nanoseconds, in long form. nanoTime() is meant for measuring relative time interval instead of providing absolute timing.

long startTime = System.nanoTime();
long estimatedTime 
  = System.nanoTime() - startTime;


